{"ts":"2026-06-22T10:58:31.892Z","author":"codex-sdk-cli-continuation","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-22T10:58:31.892Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments","value":[{"created_at":"2026-06-22T10:58:31.892Z","author":"codex-sdk-cli-continuation","text":"Evidence: Root cause from GH run 27944143257 job 82684505929: Windows Node 20 nightly failed after telemetry-otel-nonblocking functional assertions because afterAll cleanup hit EBUSY removing the temp root. The detached OTLP flush worker inherits cwd, so using the disposable temp root as cwd creates a Windows cleanup race. Patch keeps PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH sandboxed but runs spawned CLI from repoRoot, and adds fs.rm retry options for cleanup. Verification: targeted test passed (2 tests); pnpm build passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 100/100/100/100 with 242 files and 4840 tests; pnpm quality:static passed; pnpm security:scan found no credential-like secrets; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate found no known vulnerabilities; pnpm changelog:pm:check passed with pm-changelog 2026.6.20 unchanged; pm health ok; pm validate history drift ok with pre-existing resolution warnings; manual isolated temp smoke passed init/create/update/get/health. GitHub: no open PRs; GH issue #340 is the active nightly failure report; newer main CI run 27947183372 completed success including Windows Node 20."}]}],"before_hash":"c66cf822a9f234b76258b40b9d8dc8a402c0aca0e974c088d801470bb5613960","after_hash":"d3d461258016e7f99ad50f7ad11be9d2fe30419613e2cfebef22dab8a0c7f2bf"}
